</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">Representing solicitors in negotiations with regulators and government bodies.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Providing training and professional development opportunities.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">Offering guidance on ethical practices and legal standards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1">Promoting access to justice and public legal education.


</li></ul><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-32_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">According to recent statistics, the legal sector contributes approximately £60 billion annually to the UK economy, highlighting the significant impact of legal services on economic health and societal well-being.




























